TY  - JOUR
T1  - Shared and Configural Justice: A Social Network Model of Justice in Teams
AU  - Roberson, Quinetta M.
AU  - Colquitt, Jason A.
Y1  - 2005/07/01
PY  - 2005
DA  - 2005/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2005.17293715
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2005.17293715
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 595
EP  - 607
VL  - 30
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We propose a model of justice in teams that articulates the social influence processes through which shared perceptions of justice emerge and that explores the subsequent effects on team effectiveness outcomes. We also consider barriers to the emergence of shared team justice and introduce configural forms of justice that may result. Theoretical and practical contributions of the model for understanding the meaning and operation of justice at the team level of analysis are discussed.
AB  - We propose a model of justice in teams that articulates the social influence processes through which shared perceptions of justice emerge and that explores the subsequent effects on team effectiveness outcomes. We also consider barriers to the emergence of shared team justice and introduce configural forms of justice that may result. Theoretical and practical contributions of the model for understanding the meaning and operation of justice at the team level of analysis are discussed.
