T1  - A Social Interaction Model Of The Effects Of Emotion Regulation On Work Strain
AU  - CÔTÉ, STÉPHANE
Y1  - 2005/07/01
PY  - 2005
DA  - 2005/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2005.17293692
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2005.17293692
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 509
EP  - 530
VL  - 30
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Current models of how emotion regulation impacts strain focus on intraindividual processes that operate within the mind and body of the person regulating the emotion. This article presents a social interaction model of how emotion regulation impacts strain based on interpersonal processes. In this model, explanations of how emotion regulation impacts strain are based on the receiver' response to the sender' emotion regulation and display, the form of emotion regulation, and the emotion being regulated.
AB  - Current models of how emotion regulation impacts strain focus on intraindividual processes that operate within the mind and body of the person regulating the emotion. This article presents a social interaction model of how emotion regulation impacts strain based on interpersonal processes. In this model, explanations of how emotion regulation impacts strain are based on the receiver' response to the sender' emotion regulation and display, the form of emotion regulation, and the emotion being regulated.
